article.headline: Princeton 77, Harvard 71
article.story: CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- Dan Mavraides had 10 of his team-high 21 points in the final 2:20 to lead Princeton to a 77-71 win over Harvard on Saturday. Princeton (7-8, 2-0 Ivy League) made 5-of-7 shots from beyond the arc in the second half, including three treys by Mavraides and two by Doug Davis, who finished with 19 points. Jeremy Lin led Harvard (9-9, 1-3 Ivy) with 27 points, six rebounds and four assists. He scored 14 straight points for Harvard during a seven-minute stretch in the second half. Drew Housman added 15 points and six assists for Harvard. The game was tied 32-32 at halftime. Princeton took its first lead of the game, 35-32, on a 3-pointer by Davis a minute into the second half. Zach Finley and Kareem Maddox led Princeton rebounders with five apiece.
